—6. Volt, credo: Cicero admits that the verses of Solon are not really a complaint against death, yet he uses the supposed complaint. (and the contrasted indifference of Ennius) as an illustration of nec avide adpetendum, 73, 1, in a chi- astic arrangement as compared with nec sine causa deserendum and the prohibition of suicide by Pythag- oras.—6. volt . . . se esse: cf. on 32, 12.
